9 FLOOR SUBSTITUTE
10 An Act relating to the Oklahoma Employees Insurance
Plan; defining terms; requiring certain provisions to
11 be included in certain contract; prohibiting pharmacy
benefits manager (PBM) from changing drug placement
12 on a formulary without certain written authorization;
prohibiting PBM from prohibiting certain guarantees
13 of set pricing; prohibiting PBM from including
certain plan designs without certain impact analysis
14 and certain written approval of certain provisions by
state plan; prohibiting PBM from establishing certain
15 less favorable network terms; prohibiting
establishment of certain gag clauses by certain PBM;
16 prohibiting establishment of certain contract
provisions that create certain conditions that
17 exclude certain pharmacies without certain
justification; requiring PBM to disclose certain
18 affiliates or subcontractors prior to awarding of
certain contract; requiring certain rebates to be
19 passed through to state plan; construing provisions;
establishing certain determination of certain
20 guarantees; requiring PBM to maintain certain System
and Organization Controls (SOC) Type 2 certification;
21 requiring PBM to provide certain written impact
analysis prior to approval of changes to certain
22 contract provisions; requiring certain impact
analysis to include certain provisions; requiring PBM
23 to submit certain report including certain claim-
level reporting data; requiring certain report to
24 include certain provisions; allowing certain contract
Req. No. 3769 Page 1

1 proposal to be scored based on certain provisions;
providing for codification; and providing an
2 effective date.
3
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
5 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
6 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1330.1 of Title 74, unless there
7 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
8 As used in this act:
9 1. “Affiliate” means any person or entity that controls, is
10 controlled by, or is under common control with another person or
11 entity;
12 2. “Affiliated pharmacy” means any pharmacy, mail pharmacy,
13 specialty pharmacy, or pharmacy services provider that is owned,
14 operated, managed, or controlled by a pharmacy benefits manager
15 (PBM) or that otherwise shares profits or losses with the PBM or an
16 affiliate through common ownership, management, or contractual
17 arrangement;
18 3. “Control” means the possession of the power to direct or
19 cause the direction of management and policies of a person or
20 entity, whether through ownership of voting securities, by contract,
21 or otherwise. Control shall be established if a person or entity
22 owns, controls, or holds with power to vote, ten percent (10%) or
23 more of the voting securities or other ownership interest of the
24 other person or entity;
Req. No. 3769 Page 2

1 4. “Operation data” means all data and records generated,
2 received, maintained, or derived in connection with the provision of
3 PBM services to a state plan, including claims data, pricing files,
4 payment and remittance data, adjudication edits, rejection and
5 reversal data, provider network files, pharmacy contracts and
6 amendments, audit records, formulary files, utilization management
7 outputs, communications affecting benefits, and any reports derived
8 from such data;
9 5. “Rebate” means any payment, discount, credit, or price
10 concession received by a PBM, or any affiliate or subcontractor of
11 such PBM, from a drug manufacturer or such manufacturer’s affiliate,
12 in connection with utilization of a prescription drug, including
13 formulary rebates, market share rebates, performance rebates,
14 administrative fee rebates, and any other manufacturer-originated
15 remuneration;
16 6. “Remuneration” means anything of value, whether in cash or
17 in kind, paid, transferred, or provided to or for the benefit of a
18 PBM, or any affiliate or subcontractor of such PBM, in connection
19 with a prescription drug product or pharmacy benefit including, but
20 not limited to, rebates, discounts, price concessions,
21 administrative fees, services fees, data fees, network access fees,
22 market share fees, formulary placement fees, inflationary or price
23 protection payments, coupon or co-pay offset payments, dispensing or
24
Req. No. 3769 Page 3

1 tran saction fees, reconciliation payments, and any other payments in
2 cash or credit regardless of characterization;
3 7. “State plan” means the self-insured plan provided pursuant
4 to the Oklahoma Employees Insurance Plan;
5 8. “Subcontractor” means any person or entity, other than an
6 employee of the PBM that performs, delegates, supports, or
7 administers any PBM function including claims processing, network
8 administration, rebate contracting or aggregation, formulary or
9 utilization management, mail or specialty pharmacy services,
10 auditing, pricing services, or data hosting, analytics, reporting,
11 or transmission whether under a written or oral agreement;
12 9. “Total net cost” means, for a stated measurement period, the
13 sum of all amounts paid by the state plan for covered prescription
14 drugs including, but not limited to, all ingredient cost amounts,
15 dispensing fees, and any other amounts billed to the state plan and
16 all amounts paid by covered members for covered prescription drugs,
17 including co-payments, coinsurance, and deductible amounts, minus
18 all rebates and remuneration required to be passed through to the
19 state plan. Total net cost shall be calculated without regard to
20 the gross rebate volume or the list price of the drug; and
21 10. “Utilization management” means the same as defined in
22 Section 2562 of Title 63 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
